commitResults.messageTitle: Level-0: (a) renamed chatbot to 'DogeBot' (b) implemented initial skeleton message
Level-2: Add, List - store tasks & output the list of tasks
Level-3: Mark as Done - added mark task feature, created 'Task' class
Level-4: ToDos, Events, Deadlines - added 'ToDos.java', 'Deadline.java', 'Event.java' and updated 'Duke.java' to take those 3 types of tasks
dogebot logo rebrand (bc java can't compile certain ascii from prev logo)
A-TextUiTesting: implemented test cases until Level-4 features
'Duke.java' renamed to 'DogeBot.java', refactored code to switch cases (for throwing exceptions later)
Level-5: Handle Errors: DogeBot.java: handles errors for task isBlank(), invalid input, mark/unmark inputMismatch, empty list
DogeBot.java: changed 'tasks[100]' array to arraylist (for delete feature later)
DogeBot.java: updated exceptions + updated automated text-ui-testing with new features

commitResults.messageBody:
too many try-catch statements within switch-case

update code to have minimal try-catch statements

commitResults.messageTitle: Create 'tasklist.txt' for storing tasks to hard disk
commitResults.messageBody:
The tasks are stored in an array.

Storing tasks in an array doesn't save the tasks when the program reruns.

Change the storing of tasks into a .txt file instead.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update bye() method and load 'tasklist.txt' to 'tasks' arraylist
commitResults.messageBody:
Tasks are not stored in hard disk i.e 'tasklist.txt', stored in 'tasks' arraylist instead.

Task list progress is lost everytime the program is rerun.

Progress is loaded at the start into 'tasks' arraylist from 'tasklist.txt' and saved into 'tasklist.txt' when 'bye' command is entered.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update deadline feature to store date/time
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously stored deadline as string.

Deadline date/time now stored as LocalDateTime object.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update event feature to store date/time
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously stores event duration as string.

Now stores event duration as LocalDateTime objects.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bug task done marker progress
commitResults.messageBody:
Task done marker was saved into 'tasklist.txt' properly but is not loading correctly when the program starts.

Task done marker progress not tracked, shows wrong data/progress upon program start up.

Updated tasks constructors to initialise if the task has already been done, able to read progress correctly from 'tasklist.txt' now.

Code was grouped together under 'DogeBot.java'.

Didn't make complete use of OOP principles and would be harder to implement new changes.

Refactored code to extract out closely related code as classes to make use of OOP principles under 'Parser.java', 'Storage.java', 'TaskList.java' and 'Ui.java'.

No packages previously.

Gets messy to find related .java files.

Grouped all files under 'dogebot' package and tasks type files under 'tasks' package, making related types easier to find.
Set up gradle to build and run DogeBot and minor edits to code for checkstyle.

No JUnit tests previously.

Relied on text-ui-test runtest.sh test script, hard to maintain.

Added JUnit tests for non-trivial methods, easier to test/debug/maintain.

DateTimeHandler.java uses DateTimeFormat code.

Works previously but creates problems when running from 'java -jar DogeBot.jar'.

Updated constructor's read-in-from-text-file's condition to initialise LocalDateTime object without using DateTimeFormat, 'java -jar DogeBot.jar' now runs without problems.

No header comments and Java Documention previously.

Hard for viewers to interpret the purpose of each method.

Java Documentation added, easier to understand the purpose of each method at a glance.
To comply with coding standard for readability. No change in code.
Implemented a find feature to search for tasks with input keyword. Updated 'TaskTest.java' to test new hasWord() method in 'Task.java'.
